#: ../new/attacheffect.rst:6
msgid "AttachEffect"
msgstr ""

#: ../new/attacheffect.rst:8
msgid ""
"The AttachEffect system was designed as a spiritual successor to "
":game:`NPatch`'s Upgrade logic, but it was aimed to not be limited only "
"to superweapons. AttachEffect tags can be applied to both the Big Four "
"(all :type:`TechnoTypes`) and :type:`Warheads`, unless stated otherwise."
msgstr ""

#: ../new/attacheffect.rst:13
msgid ""
"The state of AttachEffects on units does not update while in a transport,"
" while under a temporal effect and so on. In this matter, they behave "
"like IvanBombs."
msgstr ""

#: ../new/attacheffect.rst
msgid "Quickstart"
msgstr ""

#: ../new/attacheffect.rst:17
msgid ""
"To create a healing/repairing or residual damage effect, attach an "
"animation with appropriate :tag:`Warhead` and :tag:`Damage` settings. "
"This will affect the target unit for the entire duration of the "
"AttachEffect, applying damage using the animation damage mechanism."
msgstr ""

#: ../new/attacheffect.rst:31
msgid ":tagdef:`[Section]AttachEffect.Animation=AnimationType`"
msgstr ""

#: ../new/attacheffect.rst:23
msgid ""
"The optional animation to play on the affected unit. The animation is "
"attached to the unit and moves along with it. Defaults to :value:`none`."
msgstr ""

#: ../new/attacheffect.rst:26
msgid ""
"The animation is removed when the unit is cloaked. The animation is "
"recreated once the unit is uncloaked again. While cloaked, the "
"AttachEffect is still applied, but the effects caused by the animation "
"are not."
msgstr ""

#: ../new/attacheffect.rst:30
msgid ""
"The animation always loops until the effect subsides. \\ :tag:`LoopCount`"
" is ignored."
msgstr ""

#: ../new/attacheffect.rst:35
msgid ":tagdef:`[Section]AttachEffect.Duration=integer - frames`"
msgstr ""

#: ../new/attacheffect.rst:34
msgid ""
"The duration of the effect in frames. Use :value:`-1` for infinite "
"duration. Defaults to :value:`0`."
msgstr ""

#: ../new/attacheffect.rst:41
msgid ":tagdef:`[Section]AttachEffect.TemporalHidesAnim=boolean`"
msgstr ""

#: ../new/attacheffect.rst:38
msgid ""
"Whether a :type:`TechnoType` with this type of AttachEffect applied on it"
" should remove the animation while being warped out by a "
":tag:`Temporal=yes` weapon. Otherwise the animation stays active and "
"unaffected by the temporal weapon. Defaults to :value:`no`."
msgstr ""

#: ../new/attacheffect.rst:44
msgid ":tagdef:`[Section]AttachEffect.SpeedMultiplier=float - multiplier`"
msgstr ""

#: ../new/attacheffect.rst:44
msgid "Speed bonus while the AttachEffect lasts. Defaults to :value:`1.0`."
msgstr ""

#: ../new/attacheffect.rst:47
msgid ":tagdef:`[Section]AttachEffect.ArmorMultiplier=float - multiplier`"
msgstr ""

#: ../new/attacheffect.rst:47
msgid "Armor bonus while the AttachEffect lasts. Defaults to :value:`1.0`."
msgstr ""

#: ../new/attacheffect.rst:61
msgid ":tagdef:`[Section]AttachEffect.FirepowerMultiplier=float - multiplier`"
msgstr ""

#: ../new/attacheffect.rst:50
msgid "Firepower bonus while the AttachEffect lasts. Defaults to :value:`1.0`."
msgstr ""

#: ../new/attacheffect.rst:52
msgid ""
"Mind that this works fundamentally differently from the other effects, "
"which are applied the instant they are needed (like a firepower for a "
"bullet impacting) as long as the effect is active: the reload time is "
"computed once when the reloading starts, but the modified reloading time "
"may take longer than the attached effect lasts."
msgstr ""

#: ../new/attacheffect.rst:58
msgid ""
"For instance, a unit that was struck with an effect slowing down the ROF "
"extremely might thus render the unit unable to fire way longer than the "
"AttachEffect is active, because the reload timer will not speed up again "
"when the effect expires."
msgstr ""

#: ../new/attacheffect.rst:65
msgid ":tagdef:`[Section]AttachEffect.ROFMultiplier=float - multiplier`"
msgstr ""

#: ../new/attacheffect.rst:64
msgid "Rate of fire bonus while the AttachEffect lasts. Defaults to :value:`1.0`."
msgstr ""

#: ../new/attacheffect.rst:69
msgid ":tagdef:`[Section]AttachEffect.Cloakable=boolean`"
msgstr ""

#: ../new/attacheffect.rst:68
msgid ""
"Whether the unit gains cloaking ability while the AttachEffect lasts. "
"Defaults to :value:`no`."
msgstr ""

#: ../new/attacheffect.rst:74
msgid ":tagdef:`[Section]AttachEffect.ForceDecloak=boolean`"
msgstr ""

#: ../new/attacheffect.rst:72
msgid ""
"Whether affected units will be forced to decloak when the AttachEffect "
"gets applied (useful for non-damaging anim-based AttachEffects). Defaults"
" to :value:`no`."
msgstr ""

#: ../new/attacheffect.rst:78
msgid ":tagdef:`[Section]AttachEffect.DiscardOnEntry=boolean`"
msgstr ""

#: ../new/attacheffect.rst:77
msgid ""
"Whether the AttachEffect will be removed when the affected unit is "
"removed from the map (entering a building or another unit). Defaults to "
":value:`no`."
msgstr ""

#: ../new/attacheffect.rst:82
msgid ":tagdef:`[Section]AttachEffect.PenetratesIronCurtain=boolean`"
msgstr ""

#: ../new/attacheffect.rst:81
msgid ""
"Whether the AttachEffect can attach to a unit or structure under the "
"influence of an Iron Curtain or Force Shield. Defaults to :value:`no`."
msgstr ""

#: ../new/attacheffect.rst:84
msgid "The following tags are valid on TechnoTypes only:"
msgstr ""

#: ../new/attacheffect.rst:89
msgid ":tagdef:`[TechnoType]AttachEffect.Delay=integer - frames`"
msgstr ""

#: ../new/attacheffect.rst:87
msgid ""
"Defines how many frames after the previous effect subsides the "
"AttachEffect is recreated on the unit itself. Negative values do not "
"renew the effect. Defaults to :value:`0` (immediately)."
msgstr ""

#: ../new/attacheffect.rst:94
msgid ":tagdef:`[TechnoType]AttachEffect.InitialDelay=integer - frames`"
msgstr ""

#: ../new/attacheffect.rst:92
msgid ""
"Defines the delay before creating the AttachEffect for the very first "
"time. Subsequent delays are defined by :tag:`AttachEffect.Delay`. Use "
":value:`0` to create effect immediately. Defaults to :value:`0`."
msgstr ""

#: ../new/attacheffect.rst:96
msgid "The following tags are valid on Warheads only:"
msgstr ""

#: ../new/attacheffect.rst:103
msgid ":tagdef:`[Warhead]AttachEffect.Cumulative=boolean`"
msgstr ""

#: ../new/attacheffect.rst:99
msgid ""
"If set to :value:`yes`, an unlimited amount of this type of AttachEffect "
"from this warhead can be applied to the target (it is stackable). If "
":value:`no`, only one instance of this type of the AttachEffect can be on"
" a single unit and that one instance gets updated if it is to be applied "
"again. Defaults to :value:`no`."
msgstr ""

#: ../new/attacheffect.rst:107
msgid ":tagdef:`[Warhead]AttachEffect.AnimResetOnReapply=boolean`"
msgstr ""

#: ../new/attacheffect.rst:106
msgid ""
"If this type of AttachEffect is not stackable, enabling this flag resets "
"the animation on every time of reapplying. Defaults to :value:`no`."
msgstr ""

